label("$2$", (B + C)/2, S);
[/asy]

Then $AO = CO = BO = r,$ so triangle $ABC$ is equilateral.  Hence, the radius of the circle is $r = \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3},$ so the area of the circle is $\frac{1}{3} \pi \left( \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3} \right)^2 = \boxed{\frac{4 \pi}{9}}.$

