Then $OC = OA = OB,$ so triangle $ABC$ is isosceles.  Furthermore, $AB = 2,$ so by the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABC,$
\[3^2 = AC^2 = BC^2 = 2^2 + AC \cdot BC.\]Hence, $AC \cdot BC = 5,$ so the area of triangle $ABC$ is
\[\sqrt{s(s - 3)(s - 3)(s - 5)},\]where $s = (2 + 3 + 3)/2 = 4.$  This simplifies to $\sqrt{2 \cdot 1 \cdot 1 \cdot 3} = \sqrt{6}.$

